3
00:01:17.247 --> 00:01:18.247
<i>[Siobhan panting]</i>

4
00:01:18.415 --> 00:01:19.581
<i>Please.</i>

5
00:01:23.720 --> 00:01:25.788
<i>No.</i>

6
00:01:26.389 --> 00:01:27.656
[cracks]

7
00:01:27.857 --> 00:01:29.324
[gasps]

8
00:01:29.526 --> 00:01:32.327
[panting]

9
00:02:11.099 --> 00:02:13.067
[laughing]

10
00:02:28.716 --> 00:02:30.617
[laughing]

11
00:02:33.955 --> 00:02:35.021
[screams]

12
00:02:35.222 --> 00:02:37.724
[clicking]

13
00:02:41.462 --> 00:02:43.597
<i>[theme music playing]</i>

14
00:03:43.754 --> 00:03:46.652
<b>3x07 - "You Can't Hide From the Dead"</b>

15
00:03:52.133 --> 00:03:55.233
<i><font color="red"> sync & correction by f1nc0
~ Addic7ed.com ~ </font></i>

16
00:03:55.534 --> 00:03:57.613
<i>[crowd cheering]</i>

17
00:04:02.174 --> 00:04:04.475
<i>Go. Charlie! Hit him!</i>

18
00:04:04.742 --> 00:04:07.010
<i>Girl: Kick his ass. man!</i>

19
00:04:07.345 --> 00:04:10.214
- Watch your back!
- I can't watch this.

20
00:04:10.515 --> 00:04:12.249
- Yeah!
- Deva. I'm gonna go home.

21
00:04:14.385 --> 00:04:15.886
Deva.

22
00:04:16.254 --> 00:04:18.354
Beaty. do whatever the
hell you want. I'm staying.

23
00:04:18.589 --> 00:04:20.924
Fine. I'm out of here.

24
00:04:21.358 --> 00:04:23.593
<i>- Girl #2: Do it!
- Boy: Hey. that's my boy right there!</i>

25
00:04:23.895 --> 00:04:26.562
Fuck this shit! Let's get real.

26
00:04:28.699 --> 00:04:30.066
<i>Charlie: Round two!</i>

27
00:04:31.968 --> 00:04:33.969
[electricity crackling]
[cheering]

28
00:04:41.578 --> 00:04:43.846
<i>Boy: Oh! Light him up!</i>

29
00:04:44.147 --> 00:04:45.782
<i>Girl #2: Yeah!
[cheering]</i>

30
00:04:48.618 --> 00:04:51.486
<i>Boy #2: Oh-ho! That's it!
[cheering]</i>

31
00:04:53.056 --> 00:04:54.389
<i>Boy #3: Yeah! Again!</i>

32
00:04:54.590 --> 00:04:56.792
[grunting]

33
00:05:26.989 --> 00:05:28.723
What the fuck are you doing here?

34
00:05:29.024 --> 00:05:30.925
I know a CI that can help find Chayton.

35
00:05:31.293 --> 00:05:33.995
<i>A former Redbone. 
Price tag's gonna be steep.</i>

36
00:05:34.330 --> 00:05:37.631
Whatever it costs. I'll get the money.
Call your informant.

37
00:05:40.201 --> 00:05:42.536
Hood.

38
00:05:42.937 --> 00:05:45.138
Should have pulled the trigger
when I had a chance.

39
00:05:55.183 --> 00:05:57.484
It's hard to shake all
that history in one moment.

40
00:05:59.854 --> 00:06:02.990
Trust me. I know.

41
00:06:16.404 --> 00:06:17.570
<i>[Stowe's voice] Colonel Douglas Sto...</i>

42
00:06:17.838 --> 00:06:19.272
[beeps]
Motherfuck!

43
00:06:19.707 --> 00:06:22.642
Wouldn't it be easier to just
use a recording of Stowe's voice?

44
00:06:22.877 --> 00:06:24.544
No. it would not.

45
00:06:25.012 --> 00:06:28.915
Stowe's voice recognition system
can identify most digital forgeries.

46
00:06:31.151 --> 00:06:32.885
<i>[Stowe's voice] Colonel Douglas Stowe.</i>

47
00:06:33.153 --> 00:06:35.754
[beeps]
But not mine.

48
00:06:36.056 --> 00:06:40.059
- All right. Then we good to go.
- We ain't even close.

49
00:06:44.030 --> 00:06:45.931
That base looks the same as it did

50
00:06:46.232 --> 00:06:48.600
the last three times you checked it.

51
00:06:50.236 --> 00:06:54.039
- No. something ain't right.
- That would be your nerves.

52
00:06:54.273 --> 00:06:57.743
- Please. I do not do nerves.
- Do you want to know what I think?

53
00:06:58.177 --> 00:07:01.112
You do know my answer to that
question never changes. right?

54
00:07:01.513 --> 00:07:04.115
There's only one way to
lay those doubts to rest.

55
00:07:04.550 --> 00:07:07.885
And it ain't sitting around
here driving yourself crazy.

56
00:07:08.087 --> 00:07:09.921
That's all.

57
00:07:38.950 --> 00:07:40.117
What?

58
00:07:45.823 --> 00:07:47.657
[muffled gasp]

59
00:07:47.925 --> 00:07:49.659
Scream and I'll kill you.

60
00:07:52.930 --> 00:07:55.098
- Is there anyone else in the house?
- Mm-mmm.

61
00:07:59.971 --> 00:08:01.738
Let's go.

62
00:08:04.475 --> 00:08:06.109
Oh...

63
00:08:10.481 --> 00:08:13.282
[breathing heavily]

64
00:08:17.954 --> 00:08:21.391
<i>Bishop: I will lift up
mine eyes unto the hills</i>

65
00:08:21.658 --> 00:08:25.661
<i>from whence cometh my help.</i>

66
00:08:25.962 --> 00:08:27.897
<i>My help cometh from the Lord</i>

67
00:08:28.164 --> 00:08:30.766
<i>which made heaven and earth.</i>

68
00:08:31.100 --> 00:08:32.968
<i>He will not suffer thy foot to be moved.</i>

69
00:08:33.302 --> 00:08:35.303
<i>He will keepeth thee
and will not slumber.</i>

70
00:08:35.605 --> 00:08:38.840
<i>Behold. He that keepeth Israel</i>

71
00:08:39.142 --> 00:08:41.876
<i>shall neither slumber nor sleep.</i>

72
00:08:43.718 --> 00:08:46.837
[music]

73
00:08:55.724 --> 00:08:59.761
Brothers. if anyone is
caught in any transgression.

74
00:09:00.062 --> 00:09:02.664
<i>you who are spiritual should restore him</i>

75
00:09:02.965 --> 00:09:05.033
<i>in a spirit of gentleness.</i>

76
00:09:19.013 --> 00:09:20.247
Welcome. Kai.

77
00:09:27.822 --> 00:09:31.124
<i>Bishop: Keep watch on yourself
lest you. too. be tempted.</i>

78
00:09:31.525 --> 00:09:34.595
<i>If anyone thinks they are
something when they are not.</i>

79
00:09:34.862 --> 00:09:37.297
<i>they deceive themselves.</i>

80
00:09:37.599 --> 00:09:40.400
<i>Each one should test their own actions.</i>

81
00:09:40.735 --> 00:09:43.336
<i>Then they can take
pride in themselves alone</i>

82
00:09:43.705 --> 00:09:45.605
<i>without comparing
themselves to someone else.</i>

83
00:09:45.906 --> 00:09:48.741
<i>For each should carry their own load.</i>

84
00:09:49.110 --> 00:09:52.011
Look. the man is 6'4" and
covered in tribal tats.

85
00:09:52.346 --> 00:09:54.214
I can't believe no one has seen him.

86
00:09:54.448 --> 00:09:57.350
No. I... I understand.

87
00:09:57.784 --> 00:10:00.353
Okay. but. look. if you hear anything.
you know where to find me.

88
00:10:00.554 --> 00:10:02.287
Thank you.

89
00:10:04.925 --> 00:10:09.128
- Any calls?
- No. sir. Slow day.

90
00:10:15.401 --> 00:10:16.836
<i>[ringing]</i>

91
00:10:17.237 --> 00:10:18.837
<i>Hi. you've reached Emily Lotus.
Please leave a message.</i>

92
00:10:19.038 --> 00:10:20.205
<i>[beeps]</i>

93
00:10:20.440 --> 00:10:23.808
Uh. hi. It's me.
Again.

94
00:10:24.110 --> 00:10:26.278
Haven't heard from you. so...

95
00:10:28.714 --> 00:10:32.231
Look. I know I'm not your most
favorite person right now. but...

96
00:10:33.653 --> 00:10:35.720
you know. I was just thinking
about us and I... Thanks!

97
00:10:36.155 --> 00:10:38.857
Uh. yeah. please return my call
at your earliest convenience.

98
00:10:45.430 --> 00:10:47.799
<i>Our friend from Philadelphia
tells me you're a little confused</i>

99
00:10:48.167 --> 00:10:50.334
<i>about the offer he
delivered from Mr. Frazier.</i>

100
00:10:53.905 --> 00:10:56.090
<i>They were buying from our
competition and you want to reward</i>

101
00:10:56.091 --> 00:10:59.000
<i>- that with a discount?
- I already agreed to Frazier's terms.</i>

102
00:11:02.013 --> 00:11:04.081
<i>Stop all sales to
the Salvadorans immediately.</i>

103
00:11:04.115 --> 00:11:06.284
<i>Is that understood?</i>

104
00:11:14.659 --> 00:11:16.110
<i>_</i>

105
00:11:16.111 --> 00:11:17.562
<i>Is that understood. Rebecca?</i>

106
00:11:39.650 --> 00:11:41.450
Does your uncle know you're here?

107
00:11:41.685 --> 00:11:42.785
That's not your concern.

108
00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:44.520
Everything is my concern.

109
00:11:44.855 --> 00:11:47.123
So tell me. why am I
having a conversation

110
00:11:47.457 --> 00:11:50.426
with the niece 
of the man who cut me off?

111
00:11:50.828 --> 00:11:53.029
I'm here to correct that
temporary error in judgment.

112
00:11:53.363 --> 00:11:55.331
What makes you think
I'd ever buy from you?

113
00:11:55.632 --> 00:11:57.466
Because you'd be a fool not to.

114
00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:01.637
Word on the street is that Frazier
is trying to put you out of business.

115
00:12:01.971 --> 00:12:07.008
You've lost control of your
street corners. your raves.

116
00:12:07.410 --> 00:12:10.312
In a couple of weeks.
you'll be shut down completely.

117
00:12:10.580 --> 00:12:13.348
I can get you back in the game.

118
00:12:18.020 --> 00:12:19.921
Can you?

119
00:12:21.690 --> 00:12:25.727
We'll start slow.
Two kilos per week at 7.000 per.

120
00:12:25.928 --> 00:12:28.363
4.000 per key.

121
00:12:43.111 --> 00:12:47.948
6.000. Or maybe you can convince
Frazier to throw you a bone.

122
00:12:49.350 --> 00:12:53.220
You guys go way back. don't you?
[sighs]

123
00:12:53.421 --> 00:12:54.889
<i>[tapping]</i>

124
00:12:57.025 --> 00:13:01.728
I like you. chica.
I really do.

125
00:13:03.197 --> 00:13:04.898
But if you fuck me.

126
00:13:05.300 --> 00:13:08.067
your uncle will be scooping
you up in tiny little pieces.

127
00:13:08.536 --> 00:13:12.639
I look forward to a long and
fruitful relationship. Mr. Morales.

128
00:13:13.874 --> 00:13:15.375
Hector.

129
00:13:15.376 --> 00:13:18.437
[music]

130
00:13:36.496 --> 00:13:39.230
[exhales]
[music stops]

131
00:13:46.800 --> 00:13:49.062
[sighs]

132
00:13:49.509 --> 00:13:53.411
Just so you know. I have been
monitoring the FBI's progress.

133
00:13:53.679 --> 00:13:56.882
Chayton is still off the grid.

134
00:13:57.150 --> 00:13:59.751
Sheriff Hood. however. is not.

135
00:14:00.119 --> 00:14:03.288
Captain Ferillo has
filed a formal complaint.

136
00:14:07.493 --> 00:14:09.594
Have you been watching Camp Genoa?

137
00:14:09.862 --> 00:14:13.598
- Did you hear what I just said?
- I did. Fuck Ferillo.

138
00:14:15.133 --> 00:14:17.001
Is there anything I should worry about?

139
00:14:17.436 --> 00:14:19.504
With all due respect. we
should all be a little worried.

140
00:14:22.174 --> 00:14:23.541
I want to delay the job.

141
00:14:26.945 --> 00:14:29.180
That base will be shut
down by the end of the week.

142
00:14:31.316 --> 00:14:33.384
It's now or never. Job.

143
00:14:36.554 --> 00:14:38.655
Well. then I guess it's never.

144
00:14:39.892 --> 00:14:40.992
What?

145
00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:45.529
Baby. I have seen every
side of you there is.

146
00:14:45.864 --> 00:14:48.999
Reckless. dumb. and especially stubborn.

147
00:14:49.300 --> 00:14:52.469
But I ain't never seen this.

148
00:14:52.704 --> 00:14:54.438
You in the deep end.

149
00:14:54.806 --> 00:14:57.741
If you don't keep your head above water.
you going to drag the rest

150
00:14:57.742 --> 00:15:00.576
- of us down there with you.
- We're doing the fucking job.

151
00:15:02.046 --> 00:15:07.294
- We're doing it tonight.
- Well. good luck with that.

152
00:15:08.552 --> 00:15:10.153
<i>Job.</i>

153
00:15:13.391 --> 00:15:15.525
You asked me what I needed.

154
00:15:17.728 --> 00:15:20.763
Right now. this is it.

155
00:15:26.169 --> 00:15:29.739
Fine.
I'll go get cleaned up.

156
00:15:30.073 --> 00:15:33.542
Might as well look pretty
for my mug shot.

157
00:15:51.894 --> 00:15:53.562
Hold.

158
00:16:06.475 --> 00:16:07.875
Okay.

159
00:16:09.311 --> 00:16:12.947
- You're not afraid of me?
- No.

160
00:16:15.217 --> 00:16:17.718
You should be.

161
00:16:17.919 --> 00:16:19.720
[scoffs]

162
00:16:19.989 --> 00:16:21.856
I buried a husband and a child.

163
00:16:22.323 --> 00:16:26.207
There are days I don't think I have
anything left to live for anyway.

164
00:16:33.290 --> 00:16:36.531
[rattling]

165
00:16:42.243 --> 00:16:45.012
- Whew!
- Well. she ain't gonna win no beauty contests.

166
00:16:45.179 --> 00:16:47.280
Thank you.

167
00:16:48.483 --> 00:16:51.051
So how is he?

168
00:16:51.319 --> 00:16:55.287
[chuckles] Same as ever.
Well. don't worry. we can count on him.

169
00:16:55.589 --> 00:16:57.396
<i>Has the waitress checked in?</i>

170
00:16:58.626 --> 00:17:01.661
Carrie hasn't checked in yet.
but she will.

171
00:17:01.929 --> 00:17:03.897
She best be on her game.

172
00:17:04.297 --> 00:17:06.866
You'd think we were knocking
over a motherfucking 7-Eleven

173
00:17:07.134 --> 00:17:08.167
the way these two are acting.

174
00:17:08.502 --> 00:17:11.437
You know what. Job?
You worry too much.

175
00:17:11.671 --> 00:17:13.506
Well. somebody's got to.

176
00:17:17.477 --> 00:17:19.734
Let's see what we got.

177
00:17:19.735 --> 00:17:21.211
[clank]

178
00:17:21.515 --> 00:17:24.716
Ooh.
That's good.

179
00:17:30.356 --> 00:17:33.124
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

180
00:17:35.127 --> 00:17:37.128
Hey. Beaty. What's up?

181
00:17:39.999 --> 00:17:43.860
What?
Where is she?

182
00:17:51.910 --> 00:17:54.279
- You sure this is the place?
- Yes.

183
00:17:54.646 --> 00:17:57.082
Any chance I can convince
you to stay out here?

184
00:17:57.316 --> 00:17:58.749
All right. then.

185
00:18:00.919 --> 00:18:02.920
Deva!

186
00:18:03.254 --> 00:18:06.090
- What the fuck?
- Carrie: We're going home now.

187
00:18:06.391 --> 00:18:07.758
What the hell are you guys doing here?

188
00:18:08.159 --> 00:18:10.327
- I'm not gonna tell you again.
- She's not going anywhere.

189
00:18:10.729 --> 00:18:12.630
- Okay. you need to shut your mouth.
- I don't believe this.

190
00:18:12.998 --> 00:18:14.264
You guys can't just
decide when to give a shit.

191
00:18:14.532 --> 00:18:15.900
- Deva!
- No. I'm staying.

192
00:18:16.401 --> 00:18:18.235
- You heard her. she's not going anywhere. man.
- Get out of my way.

193
00:18:18.536 --> 00:18:20.270
You're on my property. old man.

194
00:18:20.538 --> 00:18:22.725
And you need to fuck off now.

195
00:18:30.415 --> 00:18:31.748
Okay.

196
00:18:32.117 --> 00:18:34.884
Let's just all take a deep
breath and think about this.

197
00:18:36.887 --> 00:18:39.355
<i>- Crowd: Oh!
- You shouldn't have done that.</i>

198
00:18:41.558 --> 00:18:43.760
[crowd cheering]

199
00:19:06.783 --> 00:19:08.050
[electricity crackles]
Ah!

200
00:19:11.287 --> 00:19:12.587
[electricity crackles]
Ah!

201
00:19:29.838 --> 00:19:31.139
[shouts]

202
00:19:37.846 --> 00:19:39.413
[murmuring]

203
00:19:42.851 --> 00:19:46.420
[electricity crackling]
[groaning]

204
00:19:49.124 --> 00:19:50.658
<i>- Gordon!
- Deva: Charlie. no! Please!</i>

205
00:19:50.993 --> 00:19:52.760
- Please. don't.
- Deva. shut the fuck up!

206
00:19:57.165 --> 00:19:59.166
You man enough to
pull that trigger. son?

207
00:19:59.367 --> 00:20:00.267
I'll kill you.

208
00:20:00.468 --> 00:20:01.569
<i>Deva: Dad.</i>

209
00:20:01.836 --> 00:20:03.604
Then stop talking and do it.

210
00:20:05.307 --> 00:20:07.508
I swear. I'll shoot you. motherfucker.

211
00:20:08.610 --> 00:20:09.843
Pull it.

212
00:20:15.649 --> 00:20:17.617
Put the gun down.

213
00:20:20.888 --> 00:20:22.189
<i>[crowd gasps]</i>

214
00:20:22.456 --> 00:20:23.990
<i>Carrie: Deva. come here!</i>

215
00:20:53.319 --> 00:20:56.021
<i>Holy fuck. That's the mayor.</i>

216
00:20:56.356 --> 00:20:58.724
<i>[music playing]
[chatter]</i>

217
00:21:01.927 --> 00:21:03.395
You okay?

218
00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:10.702
I don't eat out much.

219
00:21:11.070 --> 00:21:13.805
To be honest. it's been
a while for me. too.

220
00:21:14.206 --> 00:21:16.875
Forgotten what medieval
torture high heels can be.

221
00:21:17.176 --> 00:21:18.442
You look beautiful. Emily.

222
00:21:18.778 --> 00:21:21.543
It's also been some time
since I've heard that.

223
00:21:23.115 --> 00:21:24.749
Thank you.

224
00:21:27.019 --> 00:21:30.822
Well. here we are... getting
outside of our comfort zones.

225
00:21:31.023 --> 00:21:32.757
[clinks]

226
00:21:39.798 --> 00:21:41.666
[laughs]

227
00:21:41.900 --> 00:21:46.003
You have a nice smile.
I bet not many people get to see that.

228
00:21:46.237 --> 00:21:48.606
No. No. I guess not.

229
00:21:48.940 --> 00:21:51.541
Yeah. I know what it's
like to put up walls.

230
00:21:55.479 --> 00:21:57.681
Your niece. Rebecca...

231
00:21:57.982 --> 00:21:59.749
how long has she been living with you?

232
00:22:01.286 --> 00:22:03.653
Not long.

233
00:22:03.988 --> 00:22:06.723
She was in trouble.
She needed guidance.

234
00:22:07.091 --> 00:22:10.293
And the time is coming
for her to be on her own.

235
00:22:14.164 --> 00:22:15.832
It's probably for the best.

236
00:22:42.659 --> 00:22:45.427
So do you think that's what other
family interventions are like?

237
00:22:46.763 --> 00:22:47.963
I hope so.

238
00:22:48.365 --> 00:22:50.399
I mean. why should we be the
only ones having all the fun?

239
00:22:50.667 --> 00:22:52.300
You want a small pour or big?

240
00:22:53.603 --> 00:22:55.103
Neither.

241
00:23:16.692 --> 00:23:18.359
We did good out there.

242
00:23:19.461 --> 00:23:21.562
Yeah. we did.

243
00:24:09.076 --> 00:24:11.877
[moaning]

244
00:24:36.369 --> 00:24:37.802
Where were you?

245
00:24:38.137 --> 00:24:41.639
I went for a little ride.
Hope you don't mind.

246
00:24:41.941 --> 00:24:44.276
